  "description": [
    "1 Sports News Law Enforcement Changes In Ohio COLUMBUS June 5Ohios hundred Game Protectors and Supervisors look upon their duties from very different view points than did their predeces sors of many years ago Many years ago the protectors pay depended on catching and con victing alleged violators and splitting of fees with Justices of the Peace They were not in terested and not expected to be in anything but arrests and the fees says Lester Bailey Chief of the Law Enforcement Section of the Division of Conservation A monthly report recapped from individual the Protectors latter day idea ways In which serve the cause of conservation in addition to strict enforcement which shows them to be really county conservation agents The items and totals are for the whole State More Than Arrests reports of all illustrates the of the many the field men Number of arrests 11 fisher men checked 10405 farmers contacted 5301 fur checked 17 minnow checked 116 tree units inspected 263 applications for food patches 108 pollution cases reported 27 predators destroyed winged 2751 ground 464 first air ren dered 36 meetings attended 272 Bulletin subscriptions 454 help in securing pond sites 27 license agents contacted"
